A lorry stolen from Matungulu, Machakos county, has been found dumped near industrial area estate in Naivasha. Naivasha OCPD Samuel Waweru said the vehicle's driver made a diversion whileÂ ferrying rice from the Port of Mombasa back to Machakos. He said the lorry was reported missing over the weekend so all command stations and officers at road blocks were notified. Waweru said the driver escaped but that a search was on. "The driver will help us get true information about what happened," he told reporters on Tuesday. The OCPD said the lorry had been vandalised and that several parts were missing. It was towed to Naivasha police station for safekeeping. Click here for the latest political news    